Sec. 91.067. GRADE NO. 3. Grade No. 3 onions do not meet the
requirements of a higher grade but are:
(1) sound;
(2) free from doubles, splits, bottle necks, and seed
stems;
(3) practically free from damage caused by moisture,
sunburn, cuts, disease, insects, or mechanical devices; and
(4) at least one inch in diameter.

Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

